      <hedline>
        <hl1>Man's Fate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Karl-Ludwig Selig letter notes sadly ironic juxtaposition of June 20 news article on deaths of 58 smuggled Asian immigrants and report from Berlin on rights and privileges of dogs</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''La condition humaine'' -- what tragedies, sadnesses, disparities, contrasts, ironies. A June 20 news article was headlined, ''Bodies of 58 Asians in Dover: An 'Evil Trade in People.' '' On the next page was a report from Berlin, where many a dog has more rights and privileges than many a human and ordinary citizen.</p>
        <p>KARL-LUDWIG SELIG  New York, June 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
